If you’re looking for a fun, fresh and friendly place to stay then look no further: Lisboa Central Hostel is the ideal place for you! Excellently located in the heart of city in Marques de Pombal and the famous Avenida da Liberdade this international hostel provides you with the perfect base for sight-seeing by day and partying by night.
All of Lisbon’s major hot spots are easily accessible on foot thus saving you the cab fare home at night.
Our friendly, local staff will be more than happy to provide you with plenty of information about the city and how to get around, ensuring you are able to make the most of your stay in Lisbon. The hostel is owned and run by a local Portuguese family and travellers who are able to offer you a good insight into this magical city as well as some insider’s tips on the best places to go and where to eat out.
Here at Lisboa Central Hostel we want you to feel at home and will do our utmost to ensure your stay with us is as pleasant and comfortable as possible. In doing this we have created a funky common room complete with TV, DVD and PlayStation facilities including a selection of games.
We also provide you with a fully equipped kitchen ideal for whipping up tasty meals and from where guests can enjoy our complimentary continental breakfast specially prepared by our masterchef and a picturesque terrace which is ideal for relaxing with a beer on a warm day.
In short Lisboa central Hostel is the perfect place for any traveller, whether they be the student backpacker, the young family or the more mature couple looking for a relaxing stay. As well as dorm style rooms the hostel also caters for groups and families looking for private rooms complete with en suite bathrooms.
The Hostel hosts a number of activities and cultural events including weekly film nights. And be sure not to miss out on Milkshake Monday where we will be providing each guest with a free tasty milkshake. Not to be missed, so get yours skates on and book NOW!
The hostel provides:
- FREE Wi-Fi;
- FREE Internet/ Computer access;
- FREE Breakfast from 8h to 11h;
- FREE personal lockers for guarding valuables;
- FREE fresh bed linen & towels;
- FREE use of Hairdryer;
- Guide books available to borrow;
- TV, DVDs and Playstation Games;
- FREE Maps and Advice;
- FREE Tea/Coffee Making Facilities;
- A Host of wonderful hostel Activities

